{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Call for Right to Appeal/Reverse DVSA Examiner\u2019s Decisions on ALL Driving Tests",
        "additional_details": "Call for reform of Road Traffic Act 1988, Section 133 & a new law to appeal questionable decisions by DVSA Examiners on all Driving Tests to be reversed. The Right to Appeal is an integral part of the UK constitution, derived rights from common law/Bill of Rights 1689. Candidates must have the right to call for DVSA Examiners to appear in court/tribunals as witnesses to determine outcomes of appeals, correct errors, failures & unresolved complaints. They must have the power to reverse decisions",
        "background": "Currently if a driving test candidate challenges a questionable decision by a Driver & Vehicle Standards Agency Examiner on Practical Driving Tests /ADI Tests in cars/lorries etc, the DVSA won\u2019t reverse the decision. If an appeal is successful only a retest under the Road Traffic Act 1988 is allowed",
